article.headline: Belmont 90, UT-Martin 53
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Ian Clark scored 24 of his career-high 32 points in the first half as Belmont routed Tennessee-Martin 90-53 Saturday in Ohio Valley Conference action. Clark, coming off a 30-point performance in the Bruins' 107-72 win over Southeast Missouri, was 12 of 15 from the field, including 5 of 8 3-pointers. He didn't miss in the first half, making 9 of 9 field goals, including 4 of 4 from long range, and hitting both of his foul shots. Clark scored 12 straight in one stretch as Belmont led 46-22 at halftime. The Bruins (13-4, 4-0) expanded their lead to 36, at 62-26, with 13:49 left. Craig Bradshaw scored 11, matching his career high, as Belmont shot 52.5 percent (32 of 61) and made 11 of 27 3-pointers. Myles Taylor scored 15 points and Justin Childs 14 for the Skyhawks (4-14, 1-5), who shot 29.6 percent from the field (16 of 54).
